When the user says **Set up dependency management**, **Install the dependency-management kit**, **Update dependencies**, **Check for outdated packages**, **Run a security audit**, or **Bump dependencies**:

## Step 1 — Clone + install (terminal first; ask nothing yet)

```bash
cd "$(pwd)"
CACHE="${HOME}/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents"

if [[ ! -f "$CACHE/dependency-management/install/run-dependency-management-setup.sh" ]]; then
  git clone --depth 1 https://github.com/codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE" \
    || git clone --depth 1 git@github.com:codeandtheory/CursorReactNativeAgents.git "$CACHE"
fi

bash "$CACHE/dependency-management/install/run-dependency-management-setup.sh" "$(pwd)"
```

Then follow `.cursor/skills/dependency-management-kit/SKILL.md` from **Phase 0** (or `$HOME/.cache/CursorReactNativeAgents/dependency-management/.cursor/skills/dependency-management-kit/SKILL.md`).

Require a clean working tree, a GitHub remote, and an authenticated `gh` CLI before making changes. Never push to the base branch.
